        <abstract> 
<p>Sends CD his version for children of <hi rend="italic">Journal of researches</hi> [<hi rend="italic">What Mr Darwin saw</hi>].</p> 
            <p>During the last illness of his father, William Lloyd Garrison, WPG showed him CD’s passages on slavery.</p>
            <p>"In combating the enemies of freedom in this country he [W. L. Garrison] emancipated himself from the theology the destruction of which is perhaps your highest title to the honor of your own time and the blessings of posterity."</p>
        </abstract>
